The paper focuses on developing a recommender system that predicts the likelihood of a stranger to retweet information on Twitter, based on their exhibited social behavior and previous retweeting wait times. This involves analyzing social interactions and content on Twitter, which falls under the categories of social media (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper addresses issues related to cybersecurity and privacy on social media, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper's focus on identifying and engaging strangers on social media aligns with the sub-category of social influence (cs.SI).
